  "text": "Most cardiac myxomas are sporadic. Only about 7% of them are hereditary and occur along with skin pigmentation and endocrinopathy in an autosomal dominant disorder called Carney Complex [CITATION_1] . Our patient denied any family history of cardiac tumors.",
